    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-03-30T12:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-03-30T12:40:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <head>208. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                    President’s Special Assistant (<persName type="to">Richards</persName>), at
                        Karachi<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d208fn1">Source: Department of
                        State, Central Files, 120.1580/3–2857. Secret. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_NDD1">Newsom</persName> and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName> who signed for
                            <persName>Dulles</persName>. Repeated to Baghdad, Cairo, Damascus,
                        Amman, and Jidda.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-03-30T12:40:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1957—12:40 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2492. Karachi’s 2628.<note n="2" xml:id="d208fn2">
                        <ref target="#d207">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> Department inclined agree general analysis set forth <gloss
                        target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss>. Leaders in countries you have visited
                    however strongly hope for firm alignment those supporting Doctrine and for
                    isolation Egypt and Syria. They may tend be overly optimistic about trend toward
                    isolation or results such isolation although presence Mission in area has
                    undoubtedly had some effect on situation Jordan and Syria. We believe obvious
                    effort isolate Syria and Egypt through your Mission might have contrary results
                    in Arab world, including Saudi Arabia where King has taken positive steps on our
                    behalf. Present atmosphere Egypt, Syria and Jordan does not encourage us suggest
                    you visit these countries, but we believe it too early exclude possibility. We
                    continue watch events closely with role your mission in mind and will be
                    particularly interested your recommendations following visits Iraq, Saudi Arabia
                    and Yemen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
